###Block: Combat Traits
# Ability Name	Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																		Description																																															Source Page
Hill Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Hill Fighter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are used to fighting in hilly environments. You may run or charge downhill on a steep slope (moving up to your base speed) without making an Acrobatics check to avoid stumbling - but if you travel farther than this distance, the normal rules for steep slopes apply.			SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Jungle Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Jungle Fighter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are sure-footed in jungle environments, and your speed may not be reduced to less than 10 feet by difficult terrain in jungles (meaning you may take a 5-foot step in difficult terrain and not provoke an attack of opportunity).									SOURCEPAGE:p.23
River Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,River Fighter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are used to fighting while swimming. You may swim downstream or cross-current as a charge if you make your Swim DC by 5 or more.																										SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Savanna Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Savanna Hunter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You have been trained to hunt and fight on the open plains since birth. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attacks of opportunity attack rolls made with a shortspear, as well as a +1 racial bonus on Constitution checks to continue running and avoid nonlethal damage from a forced march.	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

###Block: Magic Traits
# Ability Name	Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																		Description																																																				Source Page
Two-World Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Two-World Magic],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]	DESC:You have bridged the gap between the natural magic of the Mwangi peoples and the refined magic of the Chelish colonists. Select one 0-level spell from a class spell list other than your own. This spell is a 0-level spell on your class spell list (or a 1st-level spell if your class doesn't have 0-level spells).	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

###Block: Race Traits
# Ability Name		Category of Ability		Type				Required Ability									Multiple Requirements																			Required Race		Description																																																			Choose										Bonus to skill								Class Skill	Source Page
Adventurous Explorer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Song'o					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adventurous Explorer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]	PRERACE:1,Halfling	DESC:You are one of the few Song'o halflings to brave the world outside the Laughing Jungle. When frightened or shaken, you only take a -1 penalty on your rolls instead of -2.																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Born to the Water		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Ijo					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Born on the Water],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]		PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You were born on the shore, and you easily live on and under the water. You gain a +1 bonus on Swim checks and only need to make Swim checks once every 2 hours to avoid fatigue, instead of once each hour.																													BONUS:SKILL|Swim|1|TYPE=Trait								SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Colonial Entitlement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Chelaxian,Colonial Sargavan	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Colonial Entitlement],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]	PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You are a firm believer in the superiority of your Chelish heritage, and you cling to your racial and cultural pride. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Intimidate checks against Mwangi.																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Colonial Sympathizer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Mwangi					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Colonial Sympathizer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]	PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:Your behavior is heavily influenced by the Sargavan colonials. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Bluff and Diplomacy checks involving Sargavan colonials and others with this trait.																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Assimilated Native	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Mwangi					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Assimilated Native],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]		PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You have adopted the ways of the colonials. As a result, you feel that other, "inferior" races - such as your Mwangi brethren - should obey you as they do the colonials. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Intimidate checks to influence Mwangi natives, but you suffer a -2 on Diplomacy checks to influence them.																								SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Nomadic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Bas'o					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Nomadic],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]				PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You have lived among the Bas'o and know Sargava well. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (Geography) and Survival checks, and one of these skills (your choice) is always a class skill for you.																			CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Geography)|Survival	BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Geography),Survival|1|TYPE=Trait	CSKILL:LIST	SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Proud Tribesman		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Mwangi					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Proud Tribesman],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]		PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You may have to coexist with the colonials, but you don't have to like them. You gain a +2 bonus on checks to Intimidate colonial Sargavans.																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Slaver			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RaceTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Ombo					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Slaver],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RaceTrait]				PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:You may never have participated in a single slave raid, but members of other tribes recognize you as Ombo, and they fear and distrust you accordingly. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Intimidate checks to influence non-Ombo Mwangi, but you suffer a -2 penalty on Bluff or Diplomacy checks to influence them.																								SOURCEPAGE:p.23

